GMs dont have corpses, can TP everywhere, and aren't likely to die. Why would they get Bind Stones?<BR>
<BR>
Gimme a good reason why GMs need Binding stones, a way you can loot a GM without his consent (I mean killing him when he doesnt want to die, not /consent... anyway it doesn't work anymore), and a Binding Stone so I can take a look at it and I ll believe it.<BR>
