				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Guys, guys, guys. Bind Stones are NOT Gm only. Listen up, I speak gospel truth.<BR>
<BR>
There are THREE zones in Norrath that drop these stones. I will not say where, becuase I dont want you to know. Am I being an ass? Maybe. But I dont want everyone knowing about them. They are one of the few TRUE secrets out there. Do people know about them? Yes. I see them camped often. Not al the time, but often. That is why I wont tell. I dont want these things camped like crazy. They will lead to very mean players and will frustrate many GM's. <BR>
<BR>
How do I know about them? True, I may be a lowly level 16 Paladin, but in the guild I just formed, I have a level 3 Paladin, who has been playing since beta. He knows of ALL 3 camps. In fact, we are going up to one of them tomarrow.<BR>
<BR>
I will give THREE hints, as to where they are. Take it from here, if you wish. And remember, I swear to GOD I am not lying.<BR>
<BR>
1) It is a VERY easy camp for a level 32 Paladin.<BR>
2) One of the camps is on Antonica.<BR>
3) The camp that is in Antonica is in a southern zone.<BR>
<BR>
That is all I will say. But if you find it, PLEASE dont go spreading the word like mad, or you will NEVER get to camp it again, I guarentee. Also, if you do find the spawn, prepare to get rich. If you get some, then go to a HIGH level zone, and auction them, you will be BLASTED to offers of extreamly high prices and items.<BR>
<BR>
Good night, and good luck. Send me a tell if you wish.<BR>
<BR>
Zetatron <BR>
16 Paladin<BR>
Tribunal
